CHARTERER'S REQUIREMENTSAll above courses require refresher training / renewal at intervals not exceeding 5 years.13.8ANNEX 8 PROCEDURES TO APPLY FOR DOMESTIC SHIPPING LISCENSE (DSL) MALAYSIAThe Ministry of Transport (MOT) website is maintained in Malay language and use of “Google Translate” while making an applicationfor Domestic Shipping License (DSL) is advised. The following steps are to be followed when applying for Malaysian DSL:1) Log in to the MOT website with user ID & Password.Website is Password: executive2) Once logged in, go to “permohonanbaru” which means “New application”3) Click on “SILA PILIH KAPAL” which means “Please select vessel”. Select vessel for which DSL application is to be made from thedrop down menu. All Executive Offshore vessels are available in the dropdown box.4) Once vessel is selected press “Sahkan” to commence new DSL application for that vessel. Once selected, details of the vesselwith pre filled form will pop up on the screen.5) Enter Crew and Officers details as Malaysians & non Malaysians under the row “KAKITANGAN ATAS KAPAL COLUMN ATBOTTOM” for each category. This means crew nationality. Basically they would want to know how many Malaysian and non-Malaysiancrew on board.6) Once done, press “HANTAR” which means “submit”7) Then you are required to attach the following two documents at the bottom of the new page, “MISR Registry Certificate” and“Approved Official Crew List signed / stamped by MMD” to complete the submission process.8) Status of the application can be checked by going back to Home page and selecting icon ”“Application Status”.9) DSL approval takes 5 – 7 days. Once DSL approval status is found on the website, payment is to be made using Credit Card.10) Ask Executive Offshore Agent TOS in Labuan to collect DSL original certificate from MOT office after giving them/himauthorization letter to collect same.13.9ANNEX 9 OFFICE FORMS FILING SYSTEM
